review_blob: Pours a vibrant gold color with a nice head.  Very smooth flavor for a beer with 9% ABV.  Great spicy flavor, very long finish.

Pours a lovely golden amber color with a small, light head.  The aroma has a wonderful  whiff of honey that was unexpected.  The taste does not disappoint either, as it has a very smooth and perfectly creamy feel.  This bottle was a random purchase from Whole Foods, and I ended up being happily surprised.  Easy to drink beer with good flavor and great feel.

Pours a cloudy, deep orange color with large head.  Smells yeast and sweet.  Nice floral, peppery taste.  Amazing mouthfeel, as I didnt know a beer could feel as soft in the mouth.  Finish is a little bitter with an unoffensive alcoholic bite.

Pours a dark reddish brown, with a nice head that dissipates a little quicker than I would have liked.  Smells sweet, and it has a nice chocolate taste, but suprisingly approachable for a dark beer.  Might not please everyone, but an excellent choice for drinking.
On tap at the Seattle location.  Thin, run of the mill lager.  Tasted extremely similar to asparagus, which I didnt think was a very good thing.
Pours a cloudy, pale lemon color.  Smells of banana and spice.  Light citrusy taste; yeast is present, but not overwhelming.  Very soft feel in the mouth, but still filling.  Extremely refreshing.
Very thin, watery feel in the mouth.  Not much to this beer, except for its wide availability in the Pacific Northwest.

Pours a medium dark ruby brown.  Foams upon opening, but head dissipates quickly once in a glass.  Feels nice in the mouth, and the taste is even throughout (slight bitterness which is offset by sweetness and caramel flavors).  Not as complex as I expected, but it is a very welcoming beer.  I look forward to trying the other two Chimay brews for comparison.

Poured a beautiful gold color into a Duvel glass from a 750 mL bottle.  Nice thick, frothy head that sticks around.  Tastes a bit spicy, with some wheat and slight banana flavors.  Finishes sweet and reminds me of honey.  Alcohol is present, but doesnt feel anywhere close to the 8.5% is actually is.  Very lively; one of my favorites!
Yellow-gold color with a very cloudy appearance.  Had a very bitter finish that did not really sit well with me.
beer_name: Rogue XS Imperial India Pale Ale (IPA)

review_blob: Pours a beautiful, clear golden orange.  Very nice aroma with great citrus overtones.  Citrus comes through in the taste as well.  Beer has an oily, syrup feel in the mouth.  I havent been a huge fan of IPAs prior to having this tonight, but I can begin to see the attraction.  Aftertaste was more agreable than what I am used to with this style.
